        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 13 at 4:22PM MDT until June 13 at 5:00PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>SVRBOU

The National Weather Service in Denver has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
North Central Adams County in northeastern Colorado...
Southwestern Morgan County in northeastern Colorado...
South Central Weld County in northeastern Colorado...

* Until 500 PM MDT.

* At 422 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 8 miles east of
Prospect Valley, or 28 miles southwest of Fort Morgan, moving
northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Ping pong ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect
hail damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles.
Expect wind damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Roggen, Hoyt and Hoyt Beet Dump.
</description>
        <instruction>Seek shelter inside a well-built structure and stay away from
windows. This storm is capable of producing damaging winds and large
hail.

Tornadoes can develop quickly from severe thunderstorms. Seek
shelter immediately in an interior room on the lowest floor of a
well-built structure.</instruction>
